\f0\fs24 \cf0 CASA (Collaborative Agent Systems Architecture) is a framework for writing collaborative agents. CASA aims to support many different agent conversational paradigms, such as social commitment, BDI (Belief, Desire, Intention) and ad hoc models, and to support various standards such as the FIPA standard. But CASA also aims to avoid forcing the programmer to commit to any particular paradigm.\
